1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,500
AXIOM computes STEM answers with deterministic code,

2
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:15,000
then uses OpenAI only to explain the verified result.

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:24,000
This is the primary demo: a single-gene genetics cross, Aa times aa.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Before any AI text appears, AXIOM enumerates the exact two-by-two Punnett grid.

5
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:50,000
The genotype probabilities, fifty percent Aa, fifty percent aa,

6
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:00,000
come from direct enumeration, not from a language model.

7
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:10,000
The result is packaged as stable facts and steps.

8
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Each one has an ID, like genetics-dot-probability-dot-Aa.

9
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Those are the only evidence IDs the explanation is allowed to cite.

10
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:35,000
On the server, AXIOM recomputes the deterministic result,

11
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:45,000
sends that record to OpenAI, validates the JSON, and verifies every claim.

12
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:53,000
OpenAI adapts the wording to the learner's level and language,

13
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:00,000
it does not recalculate the cross.

14
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Citation chips link each sentence back to the evidence ledger.

15
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:15,000
A green Verified badge means every citation is valid

16
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:22,000
and every number is in the deterministic allowlist.

17
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:35,000
If a citation is missing, a number changes,

18
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:45,000
or the model output is malformed, AXIOM honestly shows Warnings

19
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:55,000
or Could not verify.

20
00:02:55,000 --> 00:03:05,000
AXIOM also ships a chat interface.

21
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Ask Aa times aa or C-of-ten-three in plain text,

22
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:35,000
the same deterministic engine answers, with the same verification badge.

23
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:50,000
No API key? The flow still works:

24
00:03:50,000 --> 00:04:05,000
AXIOM shows a clearly labeled deterministic fallback.

25
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Compute first. Explain with citations. Verify every claim.

26
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:45,000
That's AXIOM.
